summary: Note : I saw this prompt/idea on Pinterest and thought it fit with Peter and Y/n so yeah. Gifs are not mine, they belong to the...
body:
Parents (Peter Parker x reader)

Note : I saw this prompt/idea on Pinterest and thought it fit with Peter and Y/n so yeah. Gifs are not mine, they belong to the rightful owners.

Paring : Peter Parker x reader

Warnings : None

Y/n lazily glanced at the clock, impatiently tapping the table with a pen.

The bell rang signalling the end of the class.

“Finally” she rose up from her seat, gathering her notes,rushing outside the class room. Her home wasn’t that far so she started to walk with her backpack loosely hung over her right shoulder.

She stopped hearing a faint noise near the alleyway, being her curious self, Y/n decided to check it out even though the narrow alleyway seemed sullen.

She let out a gasp when she spotted a tiny puppy under the garbage bin.

“Hey, buddy, are you lost, huh?” bending down, she looked for any collar or tags on the puppy. She realised there wasn’t any.

The puppy tilted his head adorably looking at her.

“Aren’t you the cutest!” she gushed scratching his head and feeding some cookies she had in her bag.

Soon, it became a routine. She would visit him every day, buy him some food.

He will follow her back until, “Buddy, I told you” she sighed looking at him wagging his tail, “I can’t take you to my home yet, okay? I’ll tell my parents and then you can come, okay?”

Buddy wagged his tail looking up with innocent eyes.

“Good boy” she gave him another cookie and went to her home.

It went on for three weeks.

——————

Unknownest to her, Buddy, as she called her, the pupper had another care giver, a certain cute boy.

Peter found Buddy accidentally after one or his ‘missions’. Immediately taken by the puppy’s adorableness, he visited the pup every day.

Being the kind, sweetheart he is, he would play with him, offer him his food too. He got the puppy blankets too.

They enjoyed each other presence.

————-

Y/n gazed through the window eyeing the dark, gloomy clouds hiding the bright blue sky.

She immediately rushed outside,sprinting towards a certain alleyway. By the time she reached the corner,

“Buddy!” her face lit up to see him. He ran towards her wagging his tail, licking her face making her giggle.

Suddenly his ears perked up. Buddy ran past her.

Confused, she turned around to see Buddy jumping up and down around a cute boy with brown hair.

Buddy started to run towards Peter and Y/n, barking excitedly, both of his parents were there.

“Hi there” Y/n said waving at the cute guy.

“Looks like we are parents now, I’m Peter” the cute guy, Peter let out a chuckle petting Buddy.

“I’m Y/n” she smiled at Peter. Just then, it started to drizzle.

Both of them laughed as they rushed to hide from rain, outside a flower shop.

“So, what do you call him? ” Peter asked Y/n holding Buddy in his arms.

“Oh, I call him Buddy” she beamed pushing a piece of hair out of her face, tucking behind her ear.

And that was the start of a cute relationship.

question: Um, he's been seen and photographed with the kids a million times. You always claim the sighting is fake (if no photos) or photoshopped (if there are photos). There's literally nothing that could convince you that your fantasies/conspiracy theories about Ben being single and childless aren't real but infact just delusions, if Ben came to you himself with his kids to swear they were his, you'd still refuse to believe it. That's the point of delusions.
